{
  "legislative_session": "20252026",
  "identifier": "AB2645",
  "title": "Veterans: registration and identification services.",
  "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}",
  "classification": [
    "bill"
  ],
  "subject": [
    "Veterans",
    "registrationandidentificationservices"
  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Existing law establishes the Department of Veterans Affairs, which administers various programs that provide benefits to veterans, as defined. Existing law additionally establishes a statewide system of veterans' homes to provide room, board, and other services to eligible veterans and their spouses or domestic partners.\n\nExisting law establishes the Department of Motor Vehicles in the Transportation Agency and sets forth various powers and duties for the department, including prescribing and providing suitable forms of applications, certificates of ownership, registration cards, driver's licenses, and all other forms that are deemed necessary.\n\nThis bill would require the Department of Motor Vehicles, in coordination with the Department of Veterans Affairs, to provide mobile services to each resident at each California veterans' home at least once per calendar year. The bill would require the Department of Veterans Affairs to assist by coordinating the scheduling, space, and outreach to residents to facilitate the provision of those services. For the purposes of these provisions, the bill would define \"mobile services\" as, among other things, issuance or renewal of driver's licenses and identification and Real ID application processing."
    }
  ],
